condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Auditors | Description :The Recipient shall engage independent auditors for the purpose of timely carrying outof the audits not later than six (6) months after the Effective Date, in accordance with the provisions of Section III of Schedule2 of the Financing Agreement. | Due Date :30-Jun-2016

Finance Agreement :Procurement Complaint Handling Mechanism | Description :No later than three (3) months after the Effective Date,FID and the MPSPPW shall each have established a procurement complaint handling mechanism acceptable to the Association. | Due Date:10-Mar-2016

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, section 1, B 1 (b) | Description :The Recipient and the Project Implementing Agency [FID] shall, notlater than 30 days after the Effective Date, amend the Subsidiary Agreement to include the amount of the Additional Financing aswell as the activities, which have been added to the Original Project.

For the implementation of Part A.4 (a) (b) of the Project, the Project Implementing Agency shall, not later than 04 months afterthe Effective Date, enter into agreements with AGEXs and/or Payment Agencies, on the basis of the terms of reference attached tothe Urban Pilot Implementation Manual (each an “Urban Cash-Transfer Agreement”);

For the implementation of Part A.4 (a) (e) of the Project, the Project Implementing Agency shall, not later than 04 months afterthe Effective Date, enter into agreements with AGEXs and/or Payment Agencies, on the basis of the terms of reference attached tothe Urban Pilot Implementation Manual (each a “UCfW Transfer Agreement”);
